\frac{\partial z}{\partial x}(x) = \frac{\partial f}{\partial u}(\Phi(x))\cdot \frac{\partial \Phi_1}{\partial x}(x) + \frac{\partial f}{\partial v}(\Phi(x))\cdot \frac{\partial \Phi_2}{\partial x}(x).
\Phi_1(x) = x
\frac{\partial \Phi_1}{\partial x} \equiv 1
\Phi_2(x) = \phi(x)
